<% content_for :main_slider do %>
  <!-- start: Slider -->
  <div class="slider-wrapper">

    <div id="da-slider" class="da-slider">
      <div class="da-slide">
        <h2>Twitter Bootstrap</h2>
        <p>We do not brew our CSS and Javascript from ground up. Portfoliolizer is built with the latest Twitter Bootstrap themes; so you are sure that it will be cross platform compatible and always up-to-date.</p>
        <a href="#" class="da-link">Read more</a>
        <div class="da-img"><%= image_tag "parallax-slider/twitter.png", alt: "twitter" %></div>
      </div>
      <div class="da-slide">
        <h2>Responsive Design</h2>
        <p>Why have a page that only works with certain screen resolution?  With Portfoliolizer we ensure responsive pages that can be viewed at any angle!</p>
        <a href="#" class="da-link">Read more</a>
        <div class="da-img"><%= image_tag "parallax-slider/responsive.png", alt: "responsive" %></div>
      </div>
      <div class="da-slide">
        <h2>HTML5</h2>
        <p>Do you even understand what this mean?  If so; yes we use HTML5, the latest and greatest. Else; just think of HTML5 as the latest and greatest way to make your site!</p>
        <a href="#" class="da-link">Read more</a>
        <div class="da-img"><%= image_tag "parallax-slider/html5.png", alt: "html5" %></div>
      </div>
      <div class="da-slide">
        <h2>CSS3</h2>
        <p>If you love to inline style everything then Portfoliolizer will surely disappoint you. For those who don't, we got you covered with flashy CSS.</p>
        <a href="#" class="da-link">Read more</a>
        <div class="da-img"><%= image_tag "parallax-slider/css3.png", alt: "css3" %></div>
      </div>
      <nav class="da-arrows">
        <span class="da-arrows-prev"></span>
        <span class="da-arrows-next"></span>
      </nav>
    </div>

  </div>
  <!-- end: Slider -->
<% end %>

